entry.title: Implement an unprefixed mask-image property
entry.content:
This patch adds an updated and unprefixed mask-image property behind

the experimental flag CSSMaskingInterop. A new test has been added for

cases with both mask-image and -webkit-mask-image, which is important

for web compatibility. Test expectations have been updated for the

newly-passing tests. In addition to unprefixing, the patch removes

support (also behind the flag) for the non-standard cross-fade

interpolation of mask-images, which now matches both WebKit and Gecko.



The implementation approach in css_properties.json5 is novel, and is

based on a prototype by andruud@chromium.org. The approach is to add

a new flag-guarded property, "mask-image", which is a copy of the

existing "-webkit-mask-image" property. Then, a new flag-guarded

alternative of "-webkit-mask-image" is added, which is an alias of the

"mask-image" property ("-webkit-alternative-mask-image"). This ensures

that "-webkit-mask-image" uses the new "mask-image" code when the flag

is enabled. To ensure the "-webkit-mask" shorthand property uses the new

"mask-image" property, a flag-guarded alternative of "-webkit-mask" is

also added.



To remove support for interpolation, the new "mask-image" property does

not have "interpolable: true".



Bug: 432153

entry.title: arc/tracing: get smaller trace JSON to avoid ooms
entry.content:
Before this CL we were subscribed to all viz events, which generated

roughly 50MB JSON as the raw trace results for 2 minute traces. This

could not be parsed on 4GB ChromeOS devices, and 20 minute traces could

not be parsed on 8GB devices. The JSON parser would run out of memory

and the Chrome process would crash.



In the trace config, register for only one category which generates only

a single event, which is the one we care about (vsync with new frame).

This allows 4GB devices to handle the JSON for 20 minute traces. The raw

JSON output of a 2 minute trace is reduced to about 160KiB.



Remove event matchers from the mapper for other viz events which we can

no longer receive and which arc-overview-tracing does not support.



Test: Trace an app window for 1200 seconds on a 4GB RAM nautilus

entry.title: [css-masking] Use ultimate property as sorting name
entry.content:
Alternative properties (i.e. properties that use 'alternative_of')

typically have a name (defined in json5) on the form

'-alternative-foo'. However, those properties are not exposed using

their json5-declared name, instead they parse and serialize the same

as their *ultimate* property ('foo').



Our code generation did not account for this when producing an

ordered list of "computable properties", which is ultimately what

determines the enumeration order of properties in

CSSComputedStyleDeclaration.



This CL sorts properties by the ultimate property's name (i.e. the

name which is actually web-facing).



There is no behavior change in this CL, since no current properties

actually trigger the bug (due to luck). It's mainly a preparation

for the work in Issue 1418401.



Bug: 1418401

entry.title: Add SurfaceFrameType::OVERLAP
entry.content:
As part of the shelf/caption insets separation project, we need to

place caption(header) in front of(z-axis) the window area instead of

putting it above(y-axis) the area.



This commit utilizes the existing wayland protocol `setFrame` and adds

a new enum SurfaceFrameType::OVERLAP to implement this feature. To

support SurfaceFrameType::OVERLAP, the change adjusts the way to

calculate window/client bounds, and to perform nonClientHitTest.



We also considered creating a new protocol for ARC to communicate the

position of caption. However, reusing the `setFrame()` function seems to

be a better solution.

For more details see go/arc-t-caption-migration-wayland.

entry.title: Prerender: Attach TabHelpers for prerender-into-new-tab
entry.content:
This CL attaches TabHelpers to WebContents created for the

prerender-into-new-tab mode (also known as "prerendering WebContents",

see the design document below for details) by calling

TabHelpers::AttachTabHelpers().



This feature is behind the feature flag (kPrerender2InNewTab), so this

change shouldn't affect behavior in production.



> Details



The prerendering WebContents is not visible to users during prerendering

but becomes a proper browser tab on prerender activation. Therefore,

eventually it should have a full set of TabHelpers as a regular tab.

Instead of selectively attaching them to the WebContents during

prerendering, this CL attaches them all on the WebContents construction.

Some of the TabHelpers may not work during prerendering, but those cases

should be avoided by checking the lifecycle state. The CL author is now

auditing if the check is accordingly implemented in the TabHelpers:

https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1HjCoPLGgdCJbx4caKcsOeL3qIAFN0fk1wZqo3Nydqy4/edit?usp=sharing



> Design documents (Google internal):



- Overall design of the prerender-into-new-tab:

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1ZSwrsBtwgxO8xtgX0hA23YR92H62Y0o60ByVO352RL4/edit?usp=sharing



- WebContentsObserver, WebContentsDelegate, and TabHelpers on

prerendering WebContents:

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1V0LPkS_sKcrOYNkpieP2N2SJGiWp4gNLizGsx8j5fgQ/edit?usp=sharing

entry.title: Fix DirectReceiverTest.ThreadLocalInstanceShared unit tests
entry.content:
The unit test sometimes hits a nullptr exception when running this

test. Roughly 1 out of 1000 iterations on x86 when running locally.



The problem comes from the loop in

ThreadLocalNode::WatchForIncomingTransfers. The context variable is

released and if the loop actually start over we send in a nullptr when

installing the trap. We later crash in ThreadLocalNode::OnTrapEvent,

trying to use this pointer.



Fix this by only releasing the unique_ptr on successful trap

installation. The recursive call is also removed letting the loop

handle retries on its own.



R=rockot

entry.title: Revert "[a11y] Normalize the Textfield's (Views) accessible value"
entry.content:
This reverts commit 36dd531a96e001d528c80debf267904353a741ea.



Reason for revert: Breaking wmp.AdminTemplatesLaunch on multiple builders. See b/303556058 for more details.



Original change's description:

> [a11y] Normalize the Textfield's (Views) accessible value

>

> Textfields from Blink expose the display text (what's rendered on the

> screen) as the accessible value, and we do the same for all labels both

> However, the Views' Textfield class was the only class exposing the raw

subscribe method is called. It also adds some rudimentary `Observable`

constructor tests that were ported from

event handlers. Those will come in another CL. For now, this just
